e nation s leaders who will serve honorably in times of peace and peril  Every year  many of these people make a gift in support of VMI and become members of the Society of VMI Family   Friends  John J  Wranek III  85 Vice President of Annual and Reunion Giving 540 464 7287  Ext  244  Matching GiftsMany companies will double or even triple the value of charitable gifts made by employees and their spouses  board members  and retirees through matching gifts  Contact your employer to see if a matching gift program is available  John J  Wranek III  85 Vice President Annual and Reunion Giving 540 464 7287  ext  244 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  CAMPAIGN RESOURCES   Video   Campaign Cabinet   Policies VMI   Foundation   Alumni    Keydet Club UNCOMMON PURPOSE   In 1839  VMI set an uncommon course  to prepare young people for lives of service  leadership  and character  VMI cadets learn   through a rigorous military system  a demanding academic curriculum  and a robust athletic program  They leave VMI prepared to lead lives of strength  honor  and integrity   to serve their country and their communities as citizen soldiers  in times of peace and in times of deepest peril  THE CAMPAIGN FOR VMI Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7287 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org 